# Enables a minimal desktop-capable build with common system integrations and
# hardware support.
*/* -startup-notification X networkmanager fontconfig udev dbus policykit udisks joystick

# Printer and scanner
*/* cups scanner

# Graphics
*/* opengl gles2 egl

# Spell
*/* spell aspell

# Multimedia
*/* -jack v4l mtp

# - ffmpeg: Serves as the unified multimedia master engine.
# - x264 / x265 / vpx / aom: Maximizes modern streaming video playback
#   compatibility (AVC, HEVC, VP9, AV1) while fully activating GPU's hardware
#   accelerated video decoding.
# - opus / vorbis / theora / speex: Ensures structural compatibility with all
#   modern WebRTC, HTML5 video streaming, and online voice applications.
# - matroska: Explicitly passes instructions to applications to optimize
#   container structures for .mkv files.
# - dav1d: The industry reference AV1 software decoder. When hardware decoding
#   is unavailable, dav1d uses highly optimized assembly code (such as AVX2) to
#   decode high-resolution AV1 streams efficiently. This minimizes CPU
#   utilization and thermal overhead compared to alternative software decoders
#   during video playback. SVT-AV1 is primarily an encoder. Rather than enabling
#   the svt-av1 USE flag globally, it is better to enable it selectively via
#   /etc/portage/package.use/ for tools that specifically require AV1 encoding
#   capabilities, such as media-video/ffmpeg or media-video/obs-studio.
#
# REMOVED: External legacy codecs like lame, twolame, and fdk are unnecessary
# because FFmpeg handles 100% of these formats using its own native, highly
# optimized internal encoders and decoders.
# USE="$USE flac faad twolame mp3 mp4 mpeg ogg aac fdk lame"
*/* gstreamer ffmpeg x264 x265 vpx aom opus speex vorbis theora matroska dav1d

# Disable CD-ROM/DVD
# This is an optimization for a lean desktop profile. Unless the machine houses
# a physical optical disc drive, keeping CD/DVD reading and CSS decryption
# routines disabled prevents packages like mpv or ffmpeg from linking against
# hardware optical probing utilities.
*/* -cdrom -a52 -cdda -dvd -dvdr -cdr -css

# Images
*/* gif svg jpeg webp png

# Compression
*/* zlib bzip2 lzma zstd lz4 lzo zip rar

# Flatpak
*/* flatpak

# Prune massive redundant typography packages from the install plan
# I do not need 14 different font families for a clean desktop layout. GNOME
# natively relies on media-fonts/cantarell for its system shell, and the
# terminal code layouts will look crisp using media-fonts/source-code-pro or
# dejavu.
media-fonts/fonts-meta -latin

# Compiles a headless, low-overhead version of the some tools
app-text/mupdf -X
sys-apps/lshw -gtk
net-firewall/firewalld -gui
media-gfx/img2pdf -gui
net-misc/unison -gtk
